definition.value: A member of the class of  azetidines that is azetidine substituted by at least one carboxy group at unspecified position.
A 3-methylguanine that is 3,9-dihydro-6H-purin-6-one substituted by an amino group at position 2 and a methyl group at position 3.
A 3-methylguanine that is 1,2,3,9-tetrahydro-6H-purin-6-one substituted by an imino group at position 2 and a methyl group at position 3.
A 7-methylguanine that is 1,2,3,7-tetrahydro-6H-purin-6-one substituted by an imino group at position 2 and a methyl group at position 7.
A compound consisting of a peptide with attached lipid.
A 7-methylguanine that is 7H-purine substituted by an amino group at position 2, a methyl group at position 7 and a hydroxy group at position 6.
An  acetate ester that is chavicol acetate substituted by an acetoxy group at position 1'.
A dicarboxylic acid monoanion that is the conjugate base of oxalic acid.
A polar amino acid zwitterion of L-ornithine.
An L-alpha-amino acid anion that is the conjugate base of L-ornithine.
An alpha-amino-acid anion that is the conjugate base of sarcosine, arising from deprotonation of the carboxy group.
Any member of the class of dioxanes that is a cyclohexane in which two carbon atoms are replaced by oxygen atoms.
A family of aromatic fatty amides produced as secondary metabolites by chilli peppers.

A capsaicinoid that is the carboxamide resulting from the formal condensation of the amino group of 4-hydroxy-3-methoxybenzylamine with the carboxy group of nonanoic acid. It is the active ingredient in many pepper sprays.
